10. Risk Management

10.1 Technical Risks

Risk 1: Quantum Hardware Not Ready in Time

· Probability: 30%
· Impact: High
· Mitigation: Multiple technology approaches, hybrid classical-quantum solutions
· Contingency: Focus on classical AI with quantum enhancements

Risk 2: Integration with Existing Systems

· Probability: 40%
· Impact: Medium
· Mitigation: API-first design, legacy integration modules, pilot integrations
· Contingency: Parallel systems during transition

Risk 3: Accuracy Below Clinical Requirements

· Probability: 20%
· Impact: High
· Mitigation: Extensive validation, conservative deployment, human oversight
· Contingency: Use as screening tool first

Risk 4: Scale Challenges

· Probability: 50%
· Impact: Medium
· Mitigation: Design for scale, modular architecture, gradual scaling
· Contingency: Focus on high-value applications first

Risk Budget: 30% of development budget ($150B in Phase 1)

10.2 Regulatory and Ethical Risks

Regulatory Approval Delays

· Mitigation: Early regulator engagement, design for compliance, international harmonization

Privacy Concerns

· Mitigation: Privacy by design, transparent policies, patient control, quantum encryption

Ethical Concerns About Enhancement

· Mitigation: Ethical frameworks, public dialogue, therapeutic focus first

Liability and Malpractice

· Mitigation: Clear liability frameworks, insurance products, human oversight

10.3 Implementation Risks

Healthcare Professional Resistance

· Mitigation: Co-design, demonstrate benefits, extensive training, economic incentives

Patient Acceptance Issues

· Mitigation: Education, opt-out options, cultural adaptation, success stories

Infrastructure Limitations

· Mitigation: Design for low infrastructure, satellite solutions, local partnerships

Cost Higher Than Projected

· Mitigation: Aggressive cost reduction, economies of scale, value-based pricing

